2
1 received under section 811j of the Michigan vehicle code, 1949 PA
2 300, MCL 257.811j, and section 8 of the child abuse and neglect
3 prevention act, 1982 PA 250, MCL 722.608, and any amounts received
4 from civil fines imposed under the playground equipment safety act,
5 1997 PA 16, MCL 408.681 to 408.687.
6 (3) The state treasurer shall direct the investment of the
7 trust fund. The state treasurer shall have has the same authority
8 to invest the assets of the trust fund as is granted to an
9 investment fiduciary under the public employee retirement system
10 investment act, 1965 PA 314, MCL 38.1132 to 38.1141. The state
11 treasurer shall comply with the divestment from terror act, 2008 PA
12 234, MCL 129.291 to 129.301, in making investments under this act.
13 (4) Beginning in fiscal year 2015 and continuing through
14 fiscal year 2017, all money contributed to the fund that year, plus
15 4.25% of the 12-quarter rolling average of the fund, including
16 unrealized gains and losses, shall be is available for disbursement
17 upon the authorization of the state board as provided in section 9
18 of the child abuse and neglect prevention act, 1982 PA 250, MCL
19 722.609.
20 (5) Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, on
21 October 1, 2017, provided that the rolling average of the fund for
22 the previous 12 quarters, including unrealized gains and losses, is
23 at least $23,500,000.00, then, beginning with fiscal year 2018, up
24 to 5% of the 12-quarter rolling average shall must be available for
25 disbursement as specified in this subsection. On October 1, 2017,
26 if the rolling average of the fund for the previous 12 quarters,
27 including unrealized gains and losses, is less than $23,500,000.00,
28 then, beginning with fiscal year 2018, up to 4.25% of the 12-
29 quarter rolling average, including unrealized gains and losses,
