1 shall must continue to be available for disbursement. Beginning
2 with the fiscal year 2025, up to 8% of the 12-quarter rolling
3 average must be available for disbursement as specified in this
4 subsection.
5 (6) Money granted or received as gifts or donations to the
6 trust fund shall be is available for disbursement upon
7 appropriation under section 8 of the child abuse and neglect
8 prevention act, 1982 PA 250, MCL 722.608, and funds authorized for
9 expenditure shall are not be considered assets of the trust fund
10 for the purposes of subsection (4).
11 (7) The state treasurer shall annually prepare an accounting
12 of revenues and expenditures from the trust fund. This The
13 accounting shall of revenues and expenditures prepared under this
14 subsection must specifically identify the interest and earnings of
15 the trust fund, shall describe how the amount of interest and
16 earnings has been affected by the expanded investment options
17 provided for in under subsection (3), and shall identify how the
18 increased interest and earnings, if any, have been expended. This
19 The accounting shall of revenues and expenditures prepared under
20 this subsection must be provided to the senate and house of
21 representatives appropriations committees.
22 (8) As used in this section, "trust fund" means the children's
23 trust fund created in subsection (1).
24 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
25 unless all of the following bills of the 103rd Legislature are
26 enacted into law:
27 (a) Senate Bill No. 418.
28 (b) Senate Bill No. 421.
29 (c) House Bill No. 4808.
